data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both native-sized integer types work as expected:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signedSpan   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsignedSpan = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

On this 64-bit system each element is 8 bytes (`IntPtr.Size = 8`). This has been supported since C# 9 / .NET 5, when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced as first-class types backed by `System.IntPtr` / `System.UIntPtr`.
